events.name: 盗賊砦　略奪品置き場

parameters: \n< Serena >Is this where the stolen goods are kept?
エリカ HK_ST01-1
エリカ HK_ST01-1
\n< Erika >Ah, I've been dragged out here a few times...
\n< Serena >？
\n< Erika >No... it's nothing.

\n< Erika >Anyway, I saw it at that time... I'm pretty sure
it was around here...
\n< Serena >...Alcohol?

\n< Erika >Ah, the leader here is a petty guy. Gathering
distilled liquor as a thief, of all things.

\n< Erika >Distilled liquor is expensive, you know. It's not
like it's completely out of reach, but it's a bit
too casual for me.
\n< Erika >So I thought I'd take a little liberty with it...
\n< Erika >Hm, is this wine? Oh, it's a vintage.
\n< Serena >What!? Wasn't this about planning an escape?!
\n< Serena >Erika, I did say it was chaotic, but this...!

\n< Erika >No, no, of course, what I just said is actually
quite important for our escape. The key point is
the distilled liquor...

\n< Erika >There are torches conveniently placed. Quite
convenient.
\n< Serena >？？
エリカ DS_ST01-1
エリカ DS_ST01-1
\n< Erika >Cough... Cough, Ahhhchoo!... Heh! Heh! Heh!

\n< Serena >Fire... I've heard that alcohol is flammable, but
I never expected it to become such a raging
fire...

\n< Erika >It's a common trick used by sailors. Distilled
spirits, in particular, tend to burn really well.

\n< Serena >They're all in a panic because of the fire. With
this, I can easily escape by blending into the
smoke.
\n< Erika >Serves you right... Wait a moment.

\n< Erika >Oh, my equipment... abandoned in a place like
this...
\n< Erika >Inside... shit, I don't have any money or drugs...

\n< Erika >Oh! But you fool! The grenade is still intact!
This is the most valuable thing, you know!

\n< Serena >Erika-sama! If you hesitate, we will also be
engulfed in flames!

\n< Erika >I know! Damn it, I guess I have no choice but to
give up on the armor... At least the belt pouch
and the boots...

\n< Erika >Sorry, Serena! I made you wait! With this, I can
fight a little bit!!
\n< Serena >Let's go!
\n< Serena >I don't have any business on the third floor.
